{{Infobox number | number = 235 }} '''235''' ('''two hundred [and] thirty-five''') is the integer following [[234 (number)|234]] and preceding [[236 (number)|236]].
==In mathematics== '''235''' is:
*a [[semiprime]]. *a [[heptagonal number]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A000566|name=Heptagonal numbers}}</ref> *a [[centered triangular number]].<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A005448|name=Centered triangular numbers}}</ref> *therefore a [[figurate number]] in two ways. *palindromic in bases 4 (3223<sub>4</sub>), 7 (454<sub>7</sub>), 8 (353<sub>8</sub>), 13 (151<sub>13</sub>), 46 (55<sub>46</sub>) and 234 (11<sub>234</sub>) *a [[Harshad number]] in bases 6, 47, 48, 95, 116, 189 and 231. *a [[Smarandache–Wellin number]]
Also: *There are 235 different [[Tree (mathematics)|trees]] with 11 unlabeled nodes.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A000055|name=Number of trees with n unlabeled nodes}}</ref> *If an [[equilateral triangle]] is subdivided into smaller equilateral triangles whose side length is 1/9 as small, the resulting "matchstick arrangement" will have exactly 235 different equilateral triangles of varying sizes in it.<ref>{{Cite OEIS|A002717}}</ref>
==In science== *[[Uranium-235|U-235]] is the [[fissile]] [[isotope]] of [[uranium]] used in the first [[atomic bombs]].
