In mathematics, '''Angelescu polynomials''' π<sub>''n''</sub>(''x'') are generalizations of the [[Laguerre polynomials]] introduced by {{harvtxt|Angelescu|1938}} given by the [[generating function]]

:<math>\displaystyle 
\phi\left(\frac
t{1-t}\right)\exp\left(-\frac{xt}{1-t}\right)=\sum_{n=0}^\infty\pi_n(x)t^n
</math>
{{harvtxt|Boas|Buck|1958|loc=p.41}}

