'''Danny M. C. Calegari'''  (born 24 May 1972) is an [[Australia]]n-[[United States|American]] [[mathematician]] who is currently a Professor at the [[University of Chicago]]. His research interests include [[geometry]], [[dynamical systems]], [[low-dimensional topology]], and  [[geometric group theory]]. Calegari was one of the recipients of the 2009 [[Clay Research Award]] for his solution to the [[Marden tameness conjecture|Marden Tameness Conjecture]] and the [[Ahlfors measure conjecture|Ahlfors Measure Conjecture]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Research Awards {{!}} Clay Mathematics Institute|url = http://www.claymath.org/research|website = www.claymath.org|accessdate = 2015-10-29}}</ref>

==Education and early career==
In 1994, Calegari received a B.A. in Mathematics from the [[University of Melbourne]] with honors. He received his Ph.D. in 2000 from the [[University of California, Berkeley]] under the joint supervision of [[Andrew Casson]] and [[William Thurston]]; his dissertation concerned [[foliation]]s of three-dimensional [[manifold]]s.<ref>{{mathgenealogy|id=46274|name=
Danny Matthew Cornelius Calegari}}.</ref>

From 2000–2002 he was Benjamin Peirce Assistant Professor at [[Harvard University]], after which he joined the [[California Institute of Technology]] faculty; he became Merkin Professor in 2007. He was a University Professor of Pure Mathematics at the [[University of Cambridge]] in 2011–2012, and has been a Professor of Mathematics at the University of Chicago since 2012.<ref name="cv">[http://math.uchicago.edu/~dannyc/vita/vita.pdf Calegari's curriculum vitae].</ref> In 2012, he became a fellow of the [[American Mathematical Society]].<ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society], retrieved 2012-11-10.</ref>

Calegari is also an author of short fiction, published in ''[[Quadrant (magazine)|Quadrant]]'', ''Southerly'', and ''[[Overland (literary journal)|Overland]]''. His story ''A Green Light'' was a winner of a 1992 [[The Age Short Story Award]].<ref>As listed at Calegari's web page.</ref>

