In [[mathematical analysis]], a [[C0-semigroup|''C''<sub>0</sub>-semigroup]] Γ(''t''), ''t''&nbsp;≥&nbsp;0, is called a '''quasicontraction semigroup''' if there is a constant ''ω'' such that ||Γ(''t'')||&nbsp;≤&nbsp;exp(''ωt'') for all ''t''&nbsp;≥&nbsp;0. Γ(''t'') is called a '''contraction semigroup''' if ||Γ(''t'')||&nbsp;≤&nbsp;1 for all ''t''&nbsp;≥&nbsp;0.
